30/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- The Prosecutor's Office is committed to fighting corruption and crime, Attorney General Theodhori Sollaku said during a meeting Tuesday (29 October) with US Ambassador James F. 
Jeffrey. 
Sollaku also expressed appreciation for help from US experts, who have been training district attorneys in advanced investigation techniques. 
Jeffrey, meanwhile, encouraged the Prosecutor's Office to distance itself from political influence and bolster its fight against organised crime. 
(Albanian news - 30/10/02; ATA - 29/10/02)
